"{\"uid\": \"morningsun.net-stories-kaylee-mckeown-still-rules-the-olympic-backstroke-beating-regan-smith-in-womens-100-meters,143424\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"NANTERRE, France (AP) - Kaylee McKeown still rules the women's Olympic backstroke.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 0.9830506129015144, \"rank\": 0.01718097426358808, \"text\": \"NANTERRE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9325577302592896, \"rank\": 0.05660386074793645, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9984875009166625, \"rank\": 0.0015147901953383369, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 24, \"end\": 38, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian knocked off world-record holder Regan Smith of the United States in the 100 back on Tuesday night, defending the title she won at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505393517579616e-14, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 131, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3825077582736544e-26, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 150, \"end\": 163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9938145610221801, \"rank\": 0.006141710050639994, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, whobroke McKeown's world markwith a time of 57.13 seconds at the U.S. trials last month, led at the turn but could not hold off the hard-charging Aussie, who defended the title she won in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 442, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9985677117019639, \"rank\": 0.0014338250440863113, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown surged to the front about halfway through the return lap and reached for the wall in 57.33, winning by a relatively comfortable margin over Smith's finish of 57.66.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. also grabbed the bronze as Katharine Berkoff touched third in 57.98.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith reached over the lane rope to congratulate McKeown, but this one had to sting.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old Minnesota native appeared to be in top form after her performance and primed to win the first gold medal of her career.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Vikings\", \"score\": 0.7693845388487334, \"rank\": 0.20973545446617917, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Vikings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Vikings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it was McKeown capturing her fourth gold.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She swept the backstroke events in Tokyo and also claimed a gold in a relay.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9985677117019639, \"rank\": 0.0014338250440863113, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Wiffen won Ireland's first gold medal in swimming since scandal-plagued Michelle Smith finished first in three events at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9070605595694217, \"rank\": 0.04197118443140585, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9907904272605598, \"rank\": 0.009282845552981743, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.938285963873446e-13, \"text\": \"1996 Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.869379648097933e-13, \"text\": \"Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen surged past Italy's Gregorio Paltrinieri on the final lap, looking as fresh as he did at the beginning of the grueling race.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7979680409831541, \"rank\": 0.2531701421250065, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gregorio Paltrinieri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2156